      <processinfo id="aspace_f52e9339efa45f6e5890a8028d49b335">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_7fe4e15a5bb94d993d7707ecf13473ab">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of investment reports, transaction lists, disbursements, notices, posted checks, annual reports, correspondence, minutes, and research fund files documenting the operations of the Yale Cash Management Office.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <arrangement id="aspace_644343b5883723d89b7a465edc6c03d3">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
